data.enText: any of the tubes that carry blood from all parts of the body towards the heart
any of the very thin tubes that form the frame of a leaf or an insect's wing
a narrow strip of a different colour in some types of stone, wood and cheese
a thin layer of minerals or metal contained in rock
an amount of a particular quality or feature in sth

data.chText: 他们从他的秘书那里摸到了大量信息。
data.enText: They had tapped a rich vein of information in his secretary.

data.chText: 其他一些人也以类似的腔调评论。
data.enText: A number of other people commented in a similar vein .

data.chText: “那还不算全部呢。”他生气地继续说道。
data.enText: ‘And that's not all,’ he continued in angry vein.

tr: one of the horny ribs that stiffen and support the wing of an insect
a blood vessel that carries blood from the capillaries toward the heart
example: all veins except the pulmonary vein carry unaerated blood
he continued in this vein for several minutes

tr: a layer of ore between layers of rock
any of the vascular bundles or ribs that form the branching framework of conducting and supporting tissues in a leaf or other plant organ

value.def: Your veins are the thin tubes in your body through which your blood flows towards your heart.

example.ex: Many veins are found just under the skin.
example.tran: 许多静脉血管就在皮肤下面。

value.def: Something that is written or spoken in a particular vein is written or spoken in that style or mood.

example.ex: It is one  of his finest works in a lighter vein...
example.tran: 这是他行文风格轻松活泼的作品中最出色的作品之一。

example.ex: The girl now replies in similar vein.
example.tran: 这个女孩现在以相似的口吻回答。

gramarinfo.label: usu sing, with supp, usu adj N

value.tran: （行文的）风格;（说话的）语气，情绪

value.def: A vein of a particular quality is evidence of that quality which someone often shows in their behaviour or work.

example.ex: The striker's  rich vein of form this season has seen him net 32 goals...
example.tran: 这位前锋本赛季状态奇佳，进球已达到32个。

example.ex: This Spanish drama has a vein of black humour running through it.
example.tran: 这出西班牙戏剧自始至终都带有几分黑色幽默。

value.tran: 几分，若干（指在某人的行为或工作中常表现出的某种品质）

value.def: A vein of a particular metal or mineral is a layer of it lying in rock.

example.ex: ...a rich and deep vein of limestone.
example.tran: 储量丰富的深层石灰石矿脉

value.def: The veins on a leaf are the thin lines on it.

example.ex: ...the serrated edges and veins of the feathery leaves.
example.tran: 羽状叶子的锯齿边沿和纹理

trans: (尤指透过皮肤可见的)毛细血管
